      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Oct 2010 16:49:00 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[How would you like to <b>get toned abs fast</b>, easy, and without resorting to some type of fad diet or diet pills? Alright, take some time out of your day to read this article here and learn more about the 2 most effective ways to lose belly fat and get a much more toned midsection extremely fast!<br />
<br />
Okay, first things first. You must understand that in order to "see" six pack abs, your body fat percentage must be at or below 10%. Therefore, please understand that in order to get that toned look on your belly, you have to remove belly fat FIRST. Never approach this with the mindset that all you need to do is some ab crunches, leg raises, or some type of abdominal machine and BOOM... you just got yourself some abs!<br />
<br />
Now, if removing belly fat is the most important part, then what you need to focus on more than anything else is what goes in your belly... PROPER nutrition. This is the absolute most important step in your quest to get toned abs fast.<br />
<br />
What you must do is get all types of nutrients in your diet (protein, fiber, healthy fats, vitamins, minerals) without restricting ANYTHING! Therefore, I strongly recommend that you avoid fad dieting because that type of dieting will actually slow your metabolism down... which is very counterproductive since a slow metabolism causes your body to STORE fat instead of burning it off!<br />
<br />
Also, in regards to proper nutrition, make sure that you are not reducing calories too much. I recommend that you only reduce calories by no more than 300 calories below your daily maintenance calorie intake level. So, if you are supposed to get 2,000 calories daily to maintain your current weight, then reduce that number down to no less than 1,700 calories. Doing this makes sure that your metabolism will not decrease.<br />
<br />
The second most important step in order to lose belly fat... and total body fat for that matter, is to make sure that you get your metabolism elevated to the maximum peak and keep it running strong through out the entire day. The way to make that possible is to make sure that you stick with 100% natural methods for boosting the metabolism. The most natural way is with step #1 (proper nutrition).<br />
<br />
