<br />
Why?<br />
<br />
Well, the human body requires ALL types of nutrients in order to effectively work to do all of it's duties... including properly metabolizing fat. Also, the body needs a good amount of calories without you restricting too much.<br />
<br />
Restricting calories too severely will trigger your body to sense that you are starving yourself. Guess what happens if your body thinks you are starving? It is going to begin to store whatever calories you eat... AS FAT! This occurs because your metabolism is reduced during starvation and/or restricting nutrients.<br />
<br />
B.) Diet pills - Not all diet pills are bad, but I still recommend that you avoid them. Psychologically diet pills can cause you to go into the mindset that "it's okay to eat bad because you THINK the pills will remove the fat and/or reduce the calories".<br />
<br />
