      <content:encoded><![CDATA[Do you want to <b>lose midsection fat fast</b>, easy, and without having to deal with starvation, diet pills, or some type of crazy fad diet? Well, read on to discover the top 3 ways to flatten your midsection in under 1 month easily, quickly, and keep the pounds of fat off for good!<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_iBaogoSxAIo/TI-dZff_wAI/AAAAAAAACR0/4f9QQAaqKvs/s1600/abdominal+fat+reduction.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_iBaogoSxAIo/TI-dZff_wAI/AAAAAAAACR0/4f9QQAaqKvs/s320/abdominal+fat+reduction.jpg" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br />
</div><br />
1.) Lean Muscle Tissue - One of the most important ways to ensure that you'll melt away pounds of stubborn fat not only quickly and easily, but also to the point where your body will get that sexy toned look is to make sure that you are building lean muscle tissue. You see, the more lean muscle tissue you have on your body, the more your body is going to naturally burn away total body fat... even while you sleep (your body burns calories while it is repairing and growing your muscle cells).<br />
<br />
Now I'm not talking about becoming the next great HUGE bodybuilder, I'm just referring to making sure that include some form of resistance training into your workout to ensure you are building muscle. Also, I recommend that you focus on exercising just one muscle group per week to make sure that you are not over-training.<br />
<br />
2.) Protein - Now, you need to get all types of nutrients in your diet (which is why I always recommend to avoid fad diets such as those low carb, low fat, low calorie types), but making sure that you get plenty of protein is vital. The reason being is primarily directly related to #1... building lean muscle. Protein will ensure proper development of muscle tissue... which leads to quicker fat loss.<br />
<br />
The best types of proteins to get in your diet will be foods rich in lean protein. An ideal rule to go by if you are just trying to lose weight and fat is to make sure you get about 1/2 gram of protein per pound of body weight. If you are trying to build larger muscles, I recommend that you get 1 gram of protein per pound of body weight.<br />
<br />
3.) Metabolism - A surefire way to ensure you'll <a href="http://www.fatlossin11days.info/"><b>lose midsection fat fast</b></a> is to make sure you firstly don't reduce your metabolism, and to secondly, naturally boost your metabolism to the highest peak. Here are some do's and dont's for your metabolism:<br />
<br />
* The things I recommend for you to not do so that you'll prevent your metabolism from slowing down would be fad dieting, diet pills, starvation.<br />
* The things that I strongly recommend that you do to ensure you'll BOOST your metabolism is eating more frequently through out the day, adding spices to your foods, and making sure to do both weight training and cardiovascular exercises at least 4 times a week.<br />
<br />
Now, if you really want to "<a href="http://www.fatlossin11days.info/"><b>Lose Midsection Fat Fast</b></a>" and also drop 9 pounds EVERY 11 DAYS, then I highly recommend the "Calorie Shifting Diet" from Fat Loss 4 Idiots since this diet program will SKYROCKET YOUR METABOLISM to the highest peak... consistently! I lost an AMAZING 50 lbs. of fat in 8 weeks using this online plan and I did not regain 1 pound back!<br />
